This paper deals with the diversity-multiplexing tradeoff (DMT) for a wireless communication system with a relay, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses different relaying schemes and their performance, which could be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of amplify-and-forward (AF) schemes, which could be related to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of interference on the DMT, which could be relevant to the computer communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
